'''Spurius Tadius''', also '''Ludius''' or '''Studius''', was a Roman [[mural]]ist of the [[Augustus|Augustan period]]. His exact date of birth and death are unknown.

Tadius painted [[Landscape art|landscape]] murals during the reign of Augustus. He was noted for his scenes of villas and ports.<ref name="ref1">{{cite web|url=http://www.getty.edu/vow/ULANFullDisplay?find=&role=&nation=&subjectid=500057631|title=Getty Reference to Ludius|accessdate=2013-07-16}}</ref> Some manuscripts refer to him by alternate names, including Studius and Ludius.<ref name="ref2">{{cite web|url=http://ta.sandrart.net/edition/person/view/885|title=Brief Biography of Spurius Tadius (''German'')|accessdate=2013-07-16}}</ref>

